					Full Description



Travelport Worldwide Limited, incorporated on July 12, 2006, provides a travel commerce platform, which offers distribution, technology, payment, mobile and other solutions for the travel and tourism industry. The Company connects travel providers, such as airlines and hotel chains with online and offline travel agencies and other travel buyers in its business-to-business (B2B) travel commerce platform (its Travel Commerce Platform). The Company also provides a range of digital and mobile services that allow airlines, hotels, corporate travel management companies and travel agencies to engage with their customers through mobile services, including applications, corporate booking tools, mobile Web and mobile messaging. Travel Commerce Platform connects travel providers and travel buyers, as well as travel agencies, travel management companies (TMCs) and corporations.As of December 31, 2016, the Company provided air distribution services to approximately 400 airlines globally, including approximately 125 low cost carriers (LCCs). As of December 31, 2016, the Company distributed ancillaries for approximately 100 airlines. As of December 31, 2016, the Company secured content from various Beyond Air travel providers, including approximately 650,000 hotel properties (of which over 500,000 were independent hotel properties), over 37,000 car rental locations, over 50 cruise-line and tour operators and 14 rail networks across the world.As of December 31, 2016, the Company's aggregated travel content was approximately 68,000 travel agency locations representing over 234,000 online and offline travel agency terminals throughout the world. Travel Commerce Platform provides real-time search, pricing, booking, change, payment and integrated itinerary creation for travelers using the services of online and offline travel agencies for both leisure and business travel. Its access to business travelers, merchandising capabilities and ability to process complex itineraries allowed for the full integration of various LCCs, such as AirAsia, easyJet, IndiGo and Ryanair into its Travel Commerce Platform.The Company, through its eNett International (Jersey) Limited (eNett), offers a payment solution that automatically generates Mastercard numbers used to process payments. Through Locomote Holdings Pty Limited (Travelport Locomote), the Company offers both corporates and TMCs from an end-to-end customer experience perspective. Travelport Locomote is a travel platform that enables travel managers to drive change. The Travelport Locomote platform uses Travelport's universal profile, universal record, travel policy engine and its Travelport Universal application program interface (API), from which it obtains real time access to its content, which includes LCCs and network carriers, airline ancillary products, car rental and a range of hotel properties. The platform also enables integration of third-party that an individual corporation want to add to its travel and/or authorization processes, including multiple expense management systems, corporate booking tools and other add-on services, all within the user experience, workflow and data management capabilities. The Company holds interest in IGT Solutions Private Ltd. (IGTS), which is a technology development company.As of December 31, 2016, the Company utilized connections and data managed by its Travel Commerce Platform to provide advertising solutions to over 3,000 advertisers that allowed its travel providers to promote upgrades, ancillary products or services, package deals and other offers. It also offers other platform services, including subscription services, processing services, business intelligence data services and marketing-oriented analytical tools, to travel agencies, travel providers and other travel data users.The Company provides information technology (IT) solutions to airlines, such as pricing, shopping, ticketing, ground handling and other services. It also hosts reservations, inventory management and other related systems for Delta Air Lines Inc. (Delta) and runs the system infrastructure for the Delta platform in its Atlanta data center. As of December 31, 2016, the Company's global reach allowed travel providers to display and sell products in approximately 180 countries and territories and across approximately 68,000 travel agency locations representing over 234,000 online and offline travel agency terminals across the world. The Travel Commerce Platform enables travel providers to access yielding ticket prices from long-haul segments, room rates, complex itineraries and business travelers, and encourage travelers to purchase ancillary services and/or upgrade or upsell travelers through its Travelport Merchandising Suite, among others. Travelport Merchandising Suite consists of three solutions: Travelport Aggregated Shopping, Travelport Ancillary Services, and Travelport Rich Content and Branding, which offers a range of travel sales and marketing capabilities in collaboration with airlines. These solutions allow airlines to promote their products and services to the buyers.Travelport Aggregated Shopping allows travel agencies to directly compare results from network carriers delivering data through Airline Tariff Publishing Company (ATPCO), which updates global distribution systems (GDSs), with those from LCCs and other carriers using an API connection to deliver data directly and in real time to the Company. Travelport Ancillary Services allows travel agencies to sell airline ancillaries, such as checked baggage, premium seats and lounge passes, directly through their existing interface. Travelport Rich Content and Branding allows airlines to control how their flights and ancillaries are visually presented and described on travel agency screens, bringing the display in line with the airlines own Website. As of December 31, 2016, the Company provided electronic ticket distribution to 14 international and national rail networks, including Amtrak (the United States), Deutsche Bahn (Germany), Eurostar Group (the United Kingdom/France) and Societe Nationale des Chemins de Fer France (SNCF) (France).As of December 31, 2016, approximately 68,000 travel agency locations representing over 234,000 online and offline travel agency terminals across the world had used them for travel information, booking and ticketing capabilities, travel purchases, workflow automation and management tools for travel information and travel agency operations. Access to its Travel Commerce Platform enables travel agencies to electronically search travel related data, such as schedules, availability, services and prices offered by travel providers and to book travel for end customers.Travel Commerce Platform also facilitates travel agencies internal business processes, such as quality control, operations and financial information management. This includes the integration of products and services from independent parties. It also provides technical support, training and other assistance to travel agencies, including various customized access options, productivity tools, automation, training and customer support focusing on process automation, aggregation of content at the desktop and online booking solutions. In addition, it provides business intelligence and data solutions to its travel agency customers.The Company competes with Amadeus IT Group SA, Sabre Corporation, TravelSky, Infini, Sirena Travel, Concur Technologies, GetThere, Deem, KDS, eTravel, Egencia, Kayak, TripAdvisor, Yahoo! and Google.

